4.1 Installation from Melpa
===========================

‘nael’ and ‘nael-lsp’ packages are available on Melpa
(https://melpa.org/#/nael) (and Melpa-Stable
(https://stable.melpa.org/#/nael)).  To install, first add the
package-archive by adding this code to your Emacs initialization file
and evaluating it interactively.

     (require 'package)
     (add-to-list 'package-archives '("melpa" . "https://melpa.org/packages/") t)
     (package-initialize)

   Then type ‘M-x package-refresh-contents RET’.  Finally, choose one of
the following approaches: ⦿ To install interactively, type ‘M-x
package-install RET nael RET’.  ⦿ To install via package selection, add
‘(setopt package-selected-packages '(nael))’ to your init file, evaluate
it, and type ‘M-x package-install-selected-packages RET’.  ⦿ To install
via Use-Package, add ‘(use-package nael :ensure t)’ to your init file
and evaluate it.


